# loads package
rm(list = ls())
library(dml.sensemakr)
## See details in:
## - Chernozhukov, V. Cinelli, C. Newey, W. Sharma, A. Syrgkanis, V. (2021). Long Story Short: Omitted Variable Bias in Causal Machine Learning. National Bureau of Economic Research, Working Paper Series, 30302.
## - Available at: http://www.nber.org/papers/w30302
## loads data
data("pension")
y <- pension$net_tfa
d <- pension$e401
x <- model.matrix(~ -1 + age + inc + educ+ fsize + marr + twoearn + pira + hown, data = pension)

## computes income quartiles
g1 <- cut(x[,"inc"], quantile(x[,"inc"], c(0, 0.25,.5,.75,1), na.rm = TRUE),
          labels = c("q1", "q2", "q3", "q4"), include.lowest = T)


# Partially Linear Model --------------------------------------------------
dml.401k.plm <- dml(y, d, x, model = "plm")
## Debiased Machine Learning
## 
## ======================================
## Repeating 5-fold cross-fitting 1 times
## ======================================
## 
## -- Rep 1 -- Folds: 1  2  3  4  5
## Results under unconfoundedness
summary(dml.401k.plm)
## 
## Debiased Machine Learning
## 
##  Model: Partially Linear 
##  Cross-Fitting: 5 folds, 1 reps 
##  ML Method: outcome (ranger, R2 = 0.269), treatment (ranger, R2 = 0.115)
##  Tuning: clean 
## 
## Average Treatment Effect: 
## 
##     Estimate Std. Error t value   P(>|t|)    
## ate   9059.6     1324.3  6.8412 7.856e-12 ***
## ---
## Signif. codes:  0 '***' 0.001 '**' 0.01 '*' 0.05 '.' 0.1 ' ' 1
## Note: DML estimates combined using the median method.
coef(dml.401k.plm)
##      ate 
## 9059.614
se(dml.401k.plm)
##      ate 
## 1324.282
confint(dml.401k.plm)
##        2.5 %   97.5 %
## ate 6464.069 11655.16
plot(dml.401k.plm, text = F)

## senstivity results

### RV
robustness_value(dml.401k.plm)
##        ate 
## 0.05528069
### confidence bounds
confidence_bounds(dml.401k.plm, r2ya.dx = 0.03, r2.rr = 0.04, rho2 = 1)
##           lwr       upr
## ate  2640.355 15544.938
## 
## Confidence level: point = 95%; region = 90%.
## Sensitivity parameters: r2ya.dx = 0.03; r2.rr = 0.04; rho2 = 1.
### contours with bound
ovb_contour_plot(dml.401k.plm, r2ya.dx = 0.03, r2.rr = 0.04, rho2 = 1,
                 bound.label = "3x Match",
                 col.contour = "blue")

### compute estimate, SEs for all bounds, bias bound etc
bounds.plm <- dml_bounds(dml.401k.plm,  r2ya.dx = 0.03, r2.rr = 0.04, rho2 =1)
summary(bounds.plm)
## 
## Debiased Machine Learning: Bounds on Omitted Variable Bias
## 
## Sensitivity Parameters
##   r2ya.dx = 0.03
##   r2rr = 0.04
##   rho = 1 
## 
## Bounds on Average Treatment Effect: 
## 
##                Estimate Std. Error t value   P(>|t|)    
## Short Estimate  9059.61    1324.28  6.8412 7.856e-12 ***
## |Bias| Bound    4212.66     317.23 13.2796 < 2.2e-16 ***
## Lower Bound     4846.96    1341.52  3.6130 0.0003026 ***
## Upper Bound    13272.27    1381.68  9.6059 < 2.2e-16 ***
## ---
## Signif. codes:  0 '***' 0.001 '**' 0.01 '*' 0.05 '.' 0.1 ' ' 1
## 
## Note: DML estimates combined using the median method.
plot(bounds.plm, text = F)

# Nonparametric Model -----------------------------------------------------

dml.401k.npm <- dml(y, d, x, groups = g1, model = "npm")
## Debiased Machine Learning
## 
## ======================================
## Repeating 5-fold cross-fitting 1 times
## ======================================
## 
## -- Rep 1 -- Folds: 1  2  3  4  5
## Results under unconfoundedness
summary(dml.401k.npm)
## 
## Debiased Machine Learning
## 
##  Model: Nonparametric 
##  Cross-Fitting: 5 folds, 1 reps 
##  ML Method: outcome (ranger, R2 = 0.277), treatment (ranger, R2 = 0.113)
##  Tuning: clean 
## 
## Average Treatment Effect: 
## 
##     Estimate Std. Error t value   P(>|t|)    
## ate   7980.7     1184.5  6.7373 1.613e-11 ***

## gate.q1  3020.3022  6174.062
## gate.q2   212.7644  5093.378

## gate.q4 10233.8868 26164.472
plot(dml.401k.npm, text = F)

## senstivity results

### RVs
robustness_value(dml.401k.npm)
##         ate     gate.q1     gate.q2     gate.q3     gate.q4 
## 0.045783923 0.077738511 0.008548063 0.031797102 0.059690818
### confidence bounds
confidence_bounds(dml.401k.npm, r2ya.dx = 0.03, r2.rr = 0.04, rho2 = 1)
##               lwr       upr
## ate      1506.963 14524.947
## gate.q1  1861.271  7399.668
## gate.q2 -1942.093  6539.743
## gate.q3  -322.315 12972.048
## gate.q4  4955.824 31732.908
## 
## Confidence level: point = 95%; region = 90%.
## Sensitivity parameters: r2ya.dx = 0.03; r2.rr = 0.04; rho2 = 1.
### contours of lower limit with bound
ovb_contour_plot(dml.401k.npm, r2ya.dx = 0.03, r2.rr = 0.04, rho2 = 1,
                 which.bound = "lwr",
                 bound.label = "3x Match",
                 col.contour = "blue")

### you can make contours for all groups. Here's contours for group 4
ovb_contour_plot(dml.401k.npm, group = T, group.number = 4,
                 r2ya.dx = 0.03, r2.rr = 0.04, rho2 = 1,
                 which.bound = "lwr",
                 bound.label = "3x Match",
                 col.contour = "blue")

### compute estimate, SEs for all bounds, bias bound etc
bounds.npm <- dml_bounds(dml.401k.npm,  r2ya.dx = 0.03, r2.rr = 0.04, rho2 =1)
summary(bounds.npm)
